<doc>
<title><classname/></title>
<desc>
 The <classname/> class is a class that manages <midi>MIDI playback</midi><wave>PCM playback</wave><cdda>CD-DA playback</cdda>.<r/>
<wave>
 In the WaveSoundBuffer class, you can load and process .sli files created with <link href="LoopTuner" />. For details, please refer to the Loop Tuner explanation.<r/>
</wave>
</desc>

<member>
	<name><classname/></name>
	<type>constructor</type>
	<shortdesc>Construction of <classname/> object</shortdesc>
	<arg>
		<argitem>
			<name>owner</name>
			<default></default>
			<desc>
				 Specifies the event destination.<r/>
			</desc>
		</argitem>
	</arg>
	<result></result>
	<desc>
		 Constructs an object of the <classname/> class.<r/>
		 When an event occurs, the action method of the object specified by owner is called. If null is specified for owner, the action method will not be called. Usually, an object of the <ref>Window</ref> class is specified as the owner.<r/>
	</desc>
</member>


