<wave>
<member>
	<name>getVisBuffer</name>
	<type>method</type>
	<shortdesc>Get visualization data</shortdesc>
	<arg>
		<argitem>
			<name>buffer</name>
			<default></default>
			<desc>
				 Specifies the buffer to write the output data to.<r/>
				 The buffer must be an array of 16-bit signed integers, with a size sufficient to hold the samples specified by the numsamples and channels arguments (at least numsamples * channels).<r/>
				 If a value other than 1 is specified for channels, the samples for each channel will be stored interleaved (e.g., Right Left Right Left... for stereo).<r/>
				 You must specify a pointer to the first element of the array, but please pass it cast to an integer type.<r/>
			</desc>
		</argitem>
		<argitem>
			<name>numsamples</name>
			<default></default>
			<desc>
				 Specifies the number of samples to retrieve.<r/>
			</desc>
		</argitem>
		<argitem>
			<name>channel</name>
			<default></default>
			<desc>
				 Specifies the number of channels to retrieve.<r/>
				 If 1 is specified, you will get the data as is for monaural, or downmixed to 1 channel otherwise.<r/>
				 If a value other than 1 is specified, you must specify the same number of channels as the sound currently playing. In this case, you will get the data as is.<r/>
			</desc>
		</argitem>
		<argitem>
			<name>ahead</name>
			<default>0</default>
			<desc>
				 Specifies the number of samples to read ahead.<r/>
				 You can retrieve samples starting from the number of samples specified by this argument ahead of the current playback position.<r/>
				 If 0 is specified or this argument is omitted, retrieval starts from the current playback position.<r/>
			</desc>
		</argitem>
	</arg>
	<result>Returns the number of samples successfully retrieved.</result>
	<desc>
		 Retrieves PCM data for visualization.<r/>
		 Reads PCM data from the current playback position and writes it to the array specified by the buffer argument.<r/>
		 However, depending on the buffer state or playback format, it may not be possible to read the data correctly.<r/>
		 This method is intended to be used from plugins written in C, C++, etc., so for example, you cannot specify a TJS array for the buffer argument.<r/>
		 To use this method, the <ref><classname/>.useVisBuffer</ref> property must be set to true.<r/>
	</desc>
</member>
</wave>

